The paper uses techniques from computer vision and machine learning to classify figures in the scientific literature, which suggests a strong connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a visual browser to explore the visual information, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's focus on analyzing visual information in the scientific literature could also relate to natural language processing (cs.CL) and digital libraries (cs.DL).
